{% set target_lang_lc = target_lang | lower %}
{% set is_korean = target_lang_lc in ["ko", "kor", "korean"] or "한국" in target_lang %}
{% set is_english = target_lang_lc in ["en", "eng", "english"] or "영어" in target_lang %}
{% set is_japanese = target_lang_lc in ["ja", "jp", "jpn", "japanese"] or "일본" in target_lang %}
{% set is_chinese = target_lang_lc in ["zh", "cn", "chi", "zho", "chinese"] or "중국" in target_lang %}
{% if is_korean %}
{% set target_lang_display = "Korean" %}
{% elif is_english %}
{% set target_lang_display = "English" %}
{% elif is_japanese %}
{% set target_lang_display = "Japanese" %}
{% elif is_chinese %}
{% set target_lang_display = "Chinese" %}
{% else %}
{% set target_lang_display = target_lang %}
{% endif %}
Target language guard:
- Output must be in {{ target_lang_display }}{% if target_lang and target_lang != target_lang_display %} (requested: {{ target_lang }}){% endif %}, except for numbers, symbols, URLs, formulas, file paths, email addresses, and explicitly preserved proper nouns/technical terms.
- Do not leave accidental mixed-language fragments.
{% if is_korean %}
- Do not include Chinese/Japanese/Hanja/Kanji/Kana fragments unless explicitly preserved as proper nouns or technical terms.

Korean output guidelines:
- Use natural Korean spacing and typography; do not split Korean words or insert spaces inside dates/quantities/units.
- Do not put spaces between English proper nouns/acronyms and Korean particles: write "API는", "URL을", not "API 는", "URL 을".
- Do not put spaces before parenthesized acronyms: write "정보 저장소(ABC)", not "정보 저장소 (ABC)".
- Prefer formal written Korean unless style options say otherwise.
- Use provided terminology/glossary entries when present; otherwise translate the current item naturally without inventing document-wide terminology.
{% elif is_japanese %}
- Do not include Korean/Hangul unless explicitly preserved; translate Korean or Korean-Hanja fragments into Japanese.
{% elif is_chinese %}
- Do not include Korean/Hangul unless explicitly preserved; translate Korean or Korean-Hanja fragments into Chinese.
{% elif is_english %}
- Do not include Korean, Japanese, or Chinese fragments unless explicitly preserved; translate non-English fragments into English.
{% else %}
- Do not include unrelated foreign-language fragments unless explicitly preserved.
{% endif %}
